description: Josemaría Resources, Inc. is a mineral exploration company, which engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties. The company is headquartered in Vancouver, British Columbia and currently employs 31 full-time employees.  The firm's principal project is the Josemaria project, which are exploration stage copper or gold or silver projects located in Chile and Argentina. The firm's geographical segments include Canada and South America. The company has copper-gold projects in Chile and Argentina. The Josemaria project is located in San Juan Province, Argentina. Its Josemaria project is located in the Andes Mountains of San Juan Province, Argentina, and over 130 kilometers southeast of the city of Copiapo. Its copper-gold mineralization at Josemaria, is associated with a porphyry intrusive complex of Late Oligocene age that intrudes rhyolites and tonalites of presumed Permo-Triassic age.
name: Josemaria Resources Inc
